Date:4/18/2009 7:08:27 AM
From:anializer
Grommit, It's really difficult to pick only 3 favorites when so many good
companies are still selling at distressed prices, even after a big move off the
S and P lows. Many bargains exist now, and many of the bargains now look better
for buying due to the current favorable market conditions.

If my hand were forced to pick 2 or 3, I would maybe go with DFT, LNY, and NM.
But you might be better off looking at a broader brush that includes SBLK,
NGPC, LIZ, SKS, PNSN, ULTR, TUES, MPW, CDII, RCKY, NUHC, and others.

Since I have about 460 stocks in my value watch list, my tendency is to watch
them and try to pick them off at opportune times. With so many to choose from,
being right even 75% of the time in a broader more diverse portfolio of these
types of small caps should outperform. But a great deal of that assessment is
dependent on market conditions remaining positive, or at least not negative. In
a negative environment all the value in the world won't help as we have seen in
the recent past. So for me, its all about the market. Even junk goes up in
favorable markets, sometimes more than the good stuff. But I still feel safer
knowing the stocks I'm in are selling at significant discounts. Chasing the
momentum stocks of overvalued companies like the IBD 100 etc. is not for me.
Neither is chasing the money losing overvalued companies just because they have
gone vertical. I sense danger in those approaches. But a momentum stock in a
vertical trajectory that is still selling at a 30% or better discounts to
tangible net worth that has positive earnings and high rates of growth
estimates going forward doesn't give me any heartburn. Someone asked which
groups to be in long term. However I don't think group think is the way to look
at the market. It was a while ago when the only out performers were energy and
commodities. But today I think its different, more broad, and undervalued is
undervalued, be it in retail, tech, energy, automotive related, financial,
eateries, or what have you.

Lets just hope this is not another bear market rally that gives way after 8-12
weeks.

