Date:4/22/2009 12:40:00 AM
From:Spekulatius
re utilities - AEP may be worth a look. They issued some stock that is needed
to keep the rating since they are cash flow negative this year due toe heavy
investment. Still the metric look good. they own a lot of coal generating
capacity but most of it operates under a regulatory umbrella which means that
the expected cost increases from carbon caps should be a flow through item
assuming a fair (ha ha) regulatory process for rate increases.

Compare this is EIX where most coal plan are operated within the IPP part of
the EIX. The IPP' with coal plants could be really hurting due to more
competition from cheap NG and the carbon caps going forward. I am not saying
that AEP is better than EIX at this point. EIX regulatory part has gotten
decent treatment by regulators so far and they are supposed to make 2.4$ /share
this year and only 50c or so are coming from EIX IPP business. So the regulated
part is where EIX value lies, I think. Still AEP is worth a look in a basket of
utilities stocks (hopefully not a basketcase like so many of my recommendations
here).

Generally i agree that utilities look good but I'd be careful with IPP's or
diversified utilities with IPP components.
